 

Subpart 3809_Surface Management 


8. Section 3809.03 is amended by adding new paragraph (e) to read as follows: 



3809.03 

Authority. 


* * * * *


(e) The Act of October 21, 1970 (16 U.S.C. 460y 

et seq

.), as amended by Section 602 of the Federal Land Policy and Management Act of 1976 (16 U.S.C. 460y8), established
the King Range Conservation Area in California. The Secretary is required under these Acts to manage activities in
this conservation area under the General Mining Law of 1872 in such a manner as to protect the scenic, scientific, and
environmental values against undue impairment, and ensure against pollution of streams and waters. 
